                                    <p class="answer">
                                    "<span class="highlight">Scarless</span>" breast reduction is a bit of a <span class="italic">misnomer</span>—techniques like <span class="bold">liposuction</span> still leave tiny scars (about 3-4mm), but they are minimal and often hidden in natural creases. This method works well for <span class="italic">fatty breasts</span> without much excess skin or sagging. However, it doesn’t reposition the nipple or tighten skin, so it’s not ideal if you’re looking for a lift along with size reduction.
                                    </p>
