                                <div class="accordion-body">
                                    <p class="answer">
                                    The <span class="highlight">lollipop incision</span> (around the areola and vertically down) is <span class="italic">less invasive</span> than the anchor method (which adds a horizontal scar along the breast crease). It’s great for moderate reductions and offers <span class="bold">quicker recovery</span> with fewer scars. The anchor technique, however, is better suited for larger breasts or those with significant sagging since it allows more tissue removal and reshaping.
                                    </p>
